entries.journal_entry_completion_summary: Thanks to the help of Han Solo you were able to acquire a speeder for your own use.
entries.journal_entry_description: With the help of Han Solo you will be able to acquire your own speeder.
entries.task00_comm_message_text: You show a lot of promise kid, but now you're stuck on that backwater Tatooine. Tell you what, I'm going to make your life a little easier and get you a speeder.
entries.task01_journal_entry_description: Han Solo tells you there may be some wiring you can use to make your own speeder nearby. You should collect it.
entries.task02_comm_message_text: There's some more parts you'll need, look and see if you can find a power supply nearby.
entries.task03_journal_entry_description: Han Solo tells you there may be a usable power supply near the location you're at. Go check it out.
entries.task04_comm_message_text: Now you're going to need a steering array. I think there's a crashed speeder nearby that might have just the thing.
entries.task05_journal_entry_description: Han Solo says there's a speeder nearby that might have a usable steering array. You should go get it.
entries.task06_comm_message_text: Great, you just need a chassis to put it in. There's some Tusken Scavengers around that area that might just have what you need.
entries.task07_journal_entry_description: Han mentions that all you need now is a chassis. There may be some Tusken Scavengers picking clean a perfect candidate for your new speeder. Go take care of the Tuskens and get your chassis.
entries.task08_comm_message_text: You've done it, kid! You should now have a deed in your inventory. You can use it to get your speeder ready to go.
